Dear Shreya Apte,

Thank you for contacting the IBM global support center. Currently your "Microsoft Excel 2010 -Quick Test" is showing as completed. Hello Shannon,

Thank you for contacting the IBM Global Support Center. From your description it appears your test is working correctly. If you click anywhere on the test page that is not correct it will bring up the "repeat question/next question" option. We would recommend making sure you believe you have completed the question properly before hitting next question. If you do not believe that you have completed the question, click repeat and try again. You will not be able to scroll up and down or open drop down menus that don't directly correlate to the question.

If you require further instruction please feel free to contact our helpdesk via telephone at (855) 306-1669 or via email to ProveitSupport@us.ibm.com for support. Thank you!

Sincerely,

Troy

Dear Nai Saetern,

Thank you for contacting the IBM Global Support Center. Unfortunately our assessments are not compatible on chrome browsers. Please ensure that you are using Internet Explorer or Mozilla Firefox as these will be the compatible browsers for the assessments.

If you are still unable to load the assessment, you may not have the most current version of the Java program required to run the test, or you may have multiple versions conflicting with one another.

To check to see if you have Java please follow the steps listed below:
1. Click on the Start button on the lower left hand corner of your screen.
2. Click on Control Panel.
3. Select one of the following menus listed in your control panel: -Add or Remove Programs
-Programs and Features
-Un-install or Change a Program
4. Please locate anything listed that includes the word "Java".
5. Please select anything Java related and choose the option to "remove".
6. After Java is gone go to www.java.com
7. You will see an option labeled "Free Java Download". Select this and then choose to agree and start free download. If using Internet Explorer you will be given an option to run or save the file. Choose the run option. If using Mozilla Firefox, you will want to select save. The file will then appear in a window containing your recent downloads, click on the file, select run, then install.
(Please Note: At some point in the process, you may be asked to install an additional toolbar. This is not required. Please un-select the options to install and click next).
8. When you have completed the process you will see the message "You have successfully installed Java".
9. Once you receive this screen please close out of all internet windows, restart your computer, and attempt your test again.

If you require any further assistance please feel free to call us again if you experience further issues at (855) 306-1669 or email at ProveItSupport@us.ibm.com.

Thank you!

Sincerely,

Sudeep

Thank you for providing the requested information. It appears your Session ID is either invalid or has expired. Your Session ID will become expired once all assessments are in "Completed" status. In addition if the expiration date for the session has been reached (depending on company policy a session will normally be active and valid between 3 to 30 days). All results of completed assessments are sent to the company you have completed the testing for. Dear Amee Patel,

Thanks for providing the requested information. I was able to confirm that the Session ID you provided is active at this time. You will need to access the assessments from a computer and please use Internet Explorer, Mozilla Firefox or Safari (Mac) as these are the supported browsers for the testing site. Unfortunately, our Java based assessments are not compatible with Google Chrome or Microsoft Edge (Windows 10). Please access the website you were directed to in your invitation email for testing. Enter your Session ID and click "Start Session". (You only need a Session ID to log into testing.) You will then be requested to enter your personal information.Please complete the following when logging.

1. Enter your first name and then click the space bar twice and then backspace twice. Then type your last name and click the space bar twice and then backspace twice.
2. If you are using Internet Explorer, click on the Tools menu, select Internet Options. Click the Delete button that is located in the browsing history section. The only box in the next window that needs to be checked is "Form Data" and then click Delete.
3. If you are on a Macintosh (Apple) computer using Safari, click on the Safari menu then Preferences. Chose the Autofill tab and take the check mark out of other forms.

If you require further instruction please feel free to contact our help-desk via telephone at (855) 306-1669 or via email to ProveitSupport@us.ibm.com for support. Thank you!

Sincerely,
Kalyan
